## Theorem

Let $$-1 < x < 1$$,

$$
1 + x + x^2 + x^3 + x^4 + \cdots = \frac{1}{1-x}.
$$

<!--more-->
## Proof

$$
\begin{aligned}
(1 - x)(1 + x + x^2 + x^3 + x^4 + \cdots + x^k) &= 1 - x^{k+1}, \\
\lim_{k \to \infty} (1 - x)(1 + x + x^2 + x^3 + x^4 + \cdots + x^k) &= \lim_{k \to \infty} 1 - x^{k+1}, \\
(1 - x)(1 + x + x^2 + x^3 + x^4 + \cdots) &= 1.
\end{aligned}
$$
